OnPropertyChanged(string)

Raises the PropertyChanged event.

protected void OnPropertyChanged(string propertyName = "")

Parameters

propertyName string

The name of the property that changed (optional).

SetProperty<T>(ref T, T, string)

Sets the value of a property and notifies subscribers if the value changes.

protected bool SetProperty<T>(ref T field, T value, string propertyName = "")

Parameters

field T

A reference to the backing field used to hold the value of the property.

value T

The new value of the property.

propertyName string

The name of the property. It is not necessary to provide the name of the property since the CallerMemberNameAttribute has been applied on the argument. The attribute is used to automatically discover the name of the property that is changed.

Returns

bool

A bool indicating that the value of the property has been changed.

Type Parameters

T

The Type of the property to set.

Remarks

This method provides a standard approach for setting the value of a property while ensuring that the PropertyChanged event is raised if the value changes. It leverages the CallerMemberNameAttribute to automatically determine the property name, reducing the need for hardcoded strings. The method assumes that a private field backs the property and prevents unnecessary notifications when the value remains unchanged.

Events

PropertyChanged

The event raised when a property has been changed.
